Combinatorics/Derangements/Basic.html#Equiv.derangementsCongr","doc":"If `α` is equivalent to `β`, then `derangements α` is equivalent to `derangements β`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Derangements/Basic.lean#L42-L44","name":"mem_derangements_iff_fixedPoints_eq_empty","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Derangements/Basic.html#mem_derangements_iff_fixedPoints_eq_empty","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Derangements/Basic.lean#L36-L37","name":"derangements","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Derangements/Basic.html#derangements","doc":"A permutation is a derangement if it has no fixed points. "}]}